Source: No Olhar, Tue 5 Aug 2003 [edited] (Trans. by Mod.JW)
<http://www.noolhar.com/opovo/brasil/284040.html>

Brazil: 16 Hantavirus Cases Recorded in Minas Gerais
-------------------------------------------------
The Minas Gerais State Secretary of Health confirms 16 cases (8 fatal) due
to hantavirus infection in the state so far in 2003, with another 6 suspect
cases under investigation. The results of confirmatory laboratory tests
will be available in 10 days.
In all of 2002 there were 14 cases with 7 deaths. The outbreak is being
studied by specialists from the Instituto Adolfo Lutz of Sao Paulo.
--
Luz Alba Fornells, PhD
Nucleo de Investigacao em Doencas Infecciosas Emergentes - NIDIE
